commit.message:
Fixed rare misplacement of desktop icons with Qt6 (#1880)

Apparently, Qt 6.6 requires that the desktop layout to be reset after the desktop folder is loaded. Sometimes it's needed after showing the desktop too.

Also, the scope of the layer shell is set to "desktop" under Wayland (it was "window" by default).

Fixed rare misplacement of desktop icons with Qt6 (#1880)

Apparently, Qt 6.6 requires that the desktop layout to be reset after the desktop folder is loaded. Sometimes it's needed after showing the desktop too.

Also, the scope of the layer shell is set to "desktop" under Wayland (it was "window" by default).

commit.message:
Use `layer-shell-qt` for Desktop under Wayland (#1876)

Previously, workarounds provided by some Wayland compositors (like LabWC) were needed for having a usable Desktop under Wayland.

With this simple patch, and thanks to the developers of `layer-shell-qt`, PCManFM-Qt's Desktop is completely ready for Wayland. Don't forget to remove probable workarounds before using it.

Closes https://github.com/lxqt/pcmanfm-qt/issues/1871

commit.message:
Fixed a regression is setting wallpaper with command-line (#1858)

The regression resulted in an empty background when the wallpaper was set by command-line without specifying its mode, i.e., by

```
pcmanfm-qt --set-wallpaper <FILE>
```

Fixes https://github.com/lxqt/lxqt/issues/2511
